abstract: With 17 contests at stake over the next week, the night took on a frenetic pace. Sanders faced the most scrutiny yet, Warren continued to bite into her rivals and Buttigieg and Klobuchar faded.
snippet: With 17 contests at stake over the next week, the night took on a frenetic pace. Sanders faced the most scrutiny yet, Warren continued to bite into her rivals and Buttigieg and Klobuchar faded.
lead_paragraph: From the opening bell, the Democratic candidates sparred with the desperation of the looming deadline. Sixteen states and territories will vote in the next week and everyone has little time to slow the building momentum of Senator Bernie Sanders, who leads in the early delegate chase and has won the most votes in each of the first three states.

abstract: The democratic socialist found himself in the center — of the stage and the squabbling.
snippet: The democratic socialist found himself in the center — of the stage and the squabbling.
lead_paragraph: Bernie Sanders was pointing — to the left, to the right, at himself, at the sky — in one moment coming under such ubiquitous duress that he extended both hands outward, as if pushing to the front of a crowd, to swat back stage-wide accusations of fuzzy math.

abstract: Over two hours, the CBS moderating team struggled to keep control, calling for order as candidates talked over their questioners and each other.
snippet: Over two hours, the CBS moderating team struggled to keep control, calling for order as candidates talked over their questioners and each other.
lead_paragraph: Eighty-three minutes had elapsed in Tuesday night’s Democratic debate before the CBS News moderators got around to asking the candidates about coronavirus.

abstract: Candidates on the debate stage in South Carolina characterized the president’s reaction to the global crisis as chaotic and misinformed.
snippet: Candidates on the debate stage in South Carolina characterized the president’s reaction to the global crisis as chaotic and misinformed.
lead_paragraph: With the Dow Jones industrial average suffering its worst two-day loss in history on fears of the spread of the novel coronavirus, the Democratic presidential contenders on Tuesday night tried to turn the tables on President Trump in an area long perceived as one of his strengths: the economy.

abstract: Campaign veterans reacted to how the Democratic presidential candidates fared Tuesday night.
snippet: Campaign veterans reacted to how the Democratic presidential candidates fared Tuesday night.
lead_paragraph: Twitter can’t tell us whether, or how, Tuesday’s debate might change voters’ minds. lead_paragraph: Blocks from where nine people were killed in a mass shooting at a historic Charleston, S.C., black church in 2015, the Democratic presidential front-runner, Senator Bernie Sanders of Vermont, was confronted on Tuesday night about his past support for a law that gave immunity to gun manufacturers in wrongful death lawsuits.
